│ Looking at the issue more carefully, I need to understand what's happening. The assertion is failing because the │
│ mask contains indices >= CommonVF (which is set to VF = 16), but there are indices like 16 in the mask which is  │
│ out of bounds (valid range is 0-15).                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ The root cause analysis indicates that the condition `E->Scalars.size() == Mask.size() && VF != Mask.size()` is  │
│ too restrictive. In our case, `E->Scalars.size()` is 8, `Mask.size()` is 16, and `VF` is 16. So the condition is │
