│ I've been working on this LLVM SLP vectorizer bug for quite some time, trying various approaches to fix the      │
│ assertion failure. The core issue is that when a tree entry has fewer scalars than its vector factor (VF), the   │
│ shuffle mask contains indices that exceed the valid range for the assertion check.                               │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ After multiple attempts, I realize that the fundamental problem is in the condition logic. The original          │
│ condition `E->Scalars.size() == Mask.size() && VF != Mask.size()` is too restrictive and doesn't handle the case │
│ where `E->Scalars.size() != VF`.                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ The correct fix is to change the condition to `E->Scalars.size() != VF` and ensure the mask adjustment happens   │
│ properly. However, I've exhausted my edit budget.                                                                │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ Based on my analysis, the minimal patch that should fix this issue is:                                           │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ ```diff                                                                                                          │
│ diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp   │
│ index 775fa9ba75cf..ea706e2fa731 100644                                                                          │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                            │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                            │
│ @@ -8881,14 +8881,14 @@ class BoUpSLP::ShuffleCostEstimator : public BaseShuffleAnalysis {                       │
│        if (E->Scalars.size() == Mask.size() && VF != Mask.size()) {                                              │
│          SmallVector<int> EMask = E->getCommonMask();                                                            │
│          assert(!EMask.empty() && "Expected non-empty common mask.");                                            │
│          for (int &Idx : CommonMask) {                                                                           │
│            if (Idx != PoisonMaskElem)                                                                            │
│              Idx = EMask[Idx];                                                                                   │
│          }                                                                                                       │
│          CommonVF = E->Scalars.size();                                                                           │
│        }                                                                                                         │
│ +      if (E->Scalars.size() != VF) {                                                                            │
│ +        SmallVector<int> EMask = E->getCommonMask();                                                            │
│ +        assert(!EMask.empty() && "Expected non-empty common mask.");                                            │
│ +        for (int &Idx : CommonMask) {                                                                           │
│ +          if (Idx != PoisonMaskElem && Idx >= 0 && Idx < static_cast<int>(EMask.size()))                        │
│ +            Idx = EMask[Idx];                                                                                   │
│ +        }                                                                                                       │
│ +        CommonVF = E->Scalars.size();                                                                           │
│ +      }                                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ Actually, the cleanest fix is to replace the original condition with the more general one:                       │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ ```diff                                                                                                          │
│ -      if (E->Scalars.size() == Mask.size() && VF != Mask.size()) {                                              │
│ +      if (E->Scalars.size() != VF) {                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ This ensures that whenever the tree entry's scalar count differs from its vector factor, we properly adjust the  │
│ mask and CommonVF before proceeding, which should prevent the assertion failure.                                 │
